SpotiSqz connects you to Spotify and lets you see the state of your Spotify playlists and tracks at a glance. You can see how many playlists you have and what their relative sizes are. You can also view the state of another user's playlists (provided they are public). You can email yourself a list of all your playlists and tracks.
 
Tap a playlist square to see all its tracks at once. You can see which tracks are in multiple playlists, and list and visit those playlists. You can easily move tracks around within a playlist, or copy or move them to other playlists. You can bulk copy the contents of another user's playlists to one of your playlists.

If you can play music using SpotiSqz (requires Spotify premium) then SpotiSqz makes it easy to locate the tracks you want to play because you can see all your playlists at once, and all tracks at once for a playlist. 

There is also a search option which lets you search all your playlists, or scroll through your recently played tracks. SpotiSqz also shows which tracks you have already played (and can filter on this), making it easy to ensure that you have listened to everything when you are exploring a new playlist.

Repeat option lets you repeat a selected amount of times. Repeat also has the option to repeat a group of tracks.

Bit Radios is the first app in which anyone can create their own radio and as a speaker / DJ, can speak live to their listeners. It also works as a social network, where you can listen, follow and interact with other users. And the most interesting is the interaction that the app provides by allowing the radio announcer to invite other users to speak live on their radio.

How it works?
Using Apple Music or Spotify in background, the app synchronizes the DJ’s songs on their listeners devices, and then allow the exchange of audio messages which  plays instantly. The interface has a screen that shows the live radios, another to manage the radio and one to view your playlists from Spotify or Apple Music.

Why create your own radio?
Imagine that a singer you like is with his radio live, playing his personal playlist. Tap connect and you're done, you'll start listening at the same time, even listening to the comments he/her sends from time to time. And since the app allows you to invite other announcers ... who knows? you may be the next guest...

For veterans
For those who have mastered social networks, the application is an excellent sales channel. It is possible to promote companies and partner brands to your listeners. Just broadcast them in live messages.

results.description:
This game's for kids is an application for pre-school and kindergarten kids who are in early stage of identifying and learning to write English alphabets. This application helps children to memorize and learn to write in three stages:
Observe and memorize: In this step, kids learn letter writing flow and directions with pleasing animations.
Observe and trace : In this step, kids learn to write letters by tracing a guiding animation on letters.  
 
ABC  is more than just a kid-friendly educational app, it was designed with adult participation in mind, too. The interface keeps toddlers focused on alphabet reading and writing, tucking menu commands away from moving fingers. Adults can easily access settings to engage Teacher Mode, look at report cards, or toggle tracing and phonics games to better facilitate learning.

FEATURES
1 Show and enforce how to write letters correctly
2 Learn to write uppercase alphabet letters
3 Shapes tracing activity for toddlers
4 Bright, colorful graphics
5 Beautiful cartoon animation of animals
